The paper investigates the impact of different normalization layers on deep learning, specifically in ConvNets, and conducts experiments on image datasets. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of a switchable normalization method, which falls under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The experiments also involve training and optimization techniques, which could fall under the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing tasks, which could fall under the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
